external_knowledge:
- Performance of a fund category is typically determined by the aggregated performance of all funds within that category, which helps investors make informed decisions; 
- Average one-year returns are a common metric used in finance to evaluate the performance of investments over a one-year period; 
- A higher average one-year return generally indicates better performance.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(fund_id) AS total_funds_managed
FROM fund_manager_assignments
WHERE manager_id = 0;

SELECT fund_name
FROM funds
WHERE returns_1y = (SELECT MAX(returns_1y) FROM funds);
